This spontaneous report was received from a consumer and concerns a 10-year-old female patient from the United
States: 017510974A.
The patient's height, weight and medical history were not reported. 
The patient was treated with pseudoephedrine hcl (tablet, oral; unspecified frequency) 30 mg, initiated on an 
unspecified date for an unspecified indication. Concomitant medications were not reported.
On an unspecified date, the patient tried to swallow pseudoephedrine hcl and ended up chewing it because she had
never swallowed pills before (wrong technique in drug usage process).
Action taken with pseudoephedrine hcl was not reported.
